en_512135_0	59 Division troops extended their full support for conduct of the annual Katina ceremony at Kokilai Sri Sambodhi temple on Sunday (4).
en_512135_1	Ven Sri Tissapura Gunarathana Thero, Chief Incumbent at Kokilai Sri Sambodhi temple organized the proceedings with the participation of 20 Buddhist monks, attending the Heel Dana (breakfast).
en_512135_2	Mrs Chandrika and family, together with Mrs H.K Sunethra and her family members in Nugegoda assisted in numerous ways to make the religious ceremony a success.
en_512135_3	Major General Ajith Kariyakarawana, Deputy Chief of Staff also attended the occasion and planted a sapling of the Jaya Sri Maha Bodhi in the temple premises on the same day.
en_512135_4	Major General Ruwan Wanigasooriya, General Officer Commanding, 59 Division on the guidelines given by Major General Dushyantha Rajaguru, Commander, Security Forces - Mullaittivu directed his troops to support the project that went on for two days.
